**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Java's URL parser normalizes some but not all IP representations differently than HTTP libraries
- String-based host comparison misses decimal, octal, hex, and IPv6 representations
- DNS rebinding attacks can change resolution between validation and request
- URL authority parsing can be confused with @ and # characters
- Cloud metadata endpoints (169.254.169.254) can be accessed with encoded IPs

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import java.net.URL;
import java.net.URI;
import java.net.InetAddress;
import java.net.HttpURLConnection;
import java.io.BufferedReader;
import java.io.InputStreamReader;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;
import java.util.Set;
import java.util.HashSet;
import java.util.logging.Logger;

public class SecureWebhookService {

    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(SecureWebhookService.class.getName());
    private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_SCHEMES = Set.of("http", "https");
    private static final int MAX_REDIRECTS = 3;

    public String fetchWebhook(HttpServletRequest request) throws Exception {
        String urlParam = request.getParameter("url");

        // Step 1: Parse and validate URL structure
        URI uri = new URI(urlParam).normalize();

        // Step 2: Validate scheme
        String scheme = uri.getScheme();
        if (scheme == null || !ALLOWED_SCHEMES.contains(scheme.toLowerCase())) {
            logger.warning("Invalid scheme attempted: " + scheme);
            throw new SecurityException("Only HTTP/HTTPS schemes allowed");
        }

        // Step 3: Validate no userinfo (prevents user@host attacks)
        if (uri.getUserInfo() != null) {
            logger.warning("URL with userinfo rejected: " + urlParam);
            throw new SecurityException("URLs with credentials not allowed");
        }

        // Step 4: Resolve hostname to IP and validate
        String host = uri.getHost();
        if (host == null || host.isEmpty()) {
            throw new SecurityException("Invalid hostname");
        }

        // CRITICAL: Resolve DNS and check actual IP address
        if (!isHostAllowed(host)) {
            logger.warning("Blocked host access attempt: " + host);
            throw new SecurityException("Access to internal resources denied");
        }

        // Step 5: Validate port
        int port = uri.getPort();
        if (port != -1 && (port < 80 || port > 65535 || port == 22 || port == 23)) {
            throw new SecurityException("Invalid port: " + port);
        }

        // Step 6: Make request with redirect validation
        return makeSecureRequest(uri.toURL(), 0);
    }

    private boolean isHostAllowed(String host) {
        try {
            // Resolve ALL addresses for the hostname
            InetAddress[] addresses = InetAddress.getAllByName(host);

            for (InetAddress addr : addresses) {
                // Check if IP is in blocked ranges
                if (addr.isLoopbackAddress() ||
                    addr.isLinkLocalAddress() ||
                    addr.isSiteLocalAddress() ||
                    addr.isAnyLocalAddress() ||
                    addr.isMulticastAddress()) {
                    return false;
                }

                // Additional check for cloud metadata IPs
                String ip = addr.getHostAddress();
                if (ip.startsWith("169.254.") || 
                    ip.startsWith("10.") ||
                    ip.startsWith("172.16.") ||
                    ip.startsWith("192.168.")) {
                    return false;
                }
            }
            return true;
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.warning("DNS resolution failed for: " + host);
            return false; // Fail closed
        }
    }

    private String makeSecureRequest(URL url, int redirectCount) throws Exception {
        if (redirectCount > MAX_REDIRECTS) {
            throw new SecurityException("Too many redirects");
        }

        HttpURLConnection conn = (HttpURLConnection) url.openConnection();
        conn.setInstanceFollowRedirects(false); // Handle redirects manually
        conn.setRequestMethod("GET");
        conn.setConnectTimeout(5000);
        conn.setReadTimeout(5000);

        int responseCode = conn.getResponseCode();

        // Handle redirects with re-validation
        if (responseCode >= 300 && responseCode < 400) {
            String location = conn.getHeaderField("Location");
            if (location != null) {
                URL redirectUrl = new URL(url, location);
                // Re-validate the redirect destination
                if (!isHostAllowed(redirectUrl.getHost())) {
                    throw new SecurityException("Redirect to blocked host");
                }
                return makeSecureRequest(redirectUrl, redirectCount + 1);
            }
        }

        BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(
            new InputStreamReader(conn.getInputStream()));
        StringBuilder response = new StringBuilder();
        String line;
        while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {
            response.append(line);
        }
        reader.close();
        return response.toString();
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **DNS Resolution Validation**: Resolves hostname to actual IP addresses and validates each one against blocked ranges using `InetAddress` methods
- **Scheme Whitelist**: Only allows HTTP/HTTPS, blocking file://, gopher://, dict://, etc.
- **Userinfo Rejection**: Prevents URL authority confusion attacks like `http://evil.com@internal/`
- **Redirect Validation**: Manually handles redirects with re-validation to prevent redirect-based SSRF
- **Fail Closed**: Any parsing or resolution error results in denial, not bypass

DNS rebinding is a sophisticated attack where an attacker controls a DNS server that returns a legitimate IP during validation, but returns an internal IP (like 127.0.0.1) when the actual HTTP request is made. This exploits the time gap between DNS resolution for validation and resolution for the connection. Production environments need DNS pinning, socket-level validation, and network segmentation.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```java
import java.net.*;
import java.io.*;
import java.util.concurrent.*;
import java.util.logging.Logger;
import java.security.Security;
import javax.net.ssl.SSLSocketFactory;
import javax.net.ssl.HttpsURLConnection;
import com.google.common.cache.Cache;
import com.google.common.cache.CacheBuilder;
import io.micrometer.core.instrument.Counter;
import io.micrometer.core.instrument.MeterRegistry;
import io.micrometer.core.instrument.Timer;

public class ProductionSSRFSafeClient {

    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(ProductionSSRFSafeClient.class.getName());

    // DNS cache to prevent rebinding between validation and request
    private final Cache<String, InetAddress[]> dnsCache;

    // Rate limiter per source
    private final ConcurrentHashMap<String, RateLimiter> rateLimiters;

    // Metrics
    private final Counter ssrfBlockedCounter;
    private final Counter dnsRebindingAttempts;
    private final Timer requestTimer;

    // Configuration
    private static final int DNS_CACHE_TTL_SECONDS = 300;
    private static final int MAX_REQUESTS_PER_MINUTE = 60;
    private static final int CONNECTION_TIMEOUT_MS = 3000;
    private static final int READ_TIMEOUT_MS = 5000;
    private static final int MAX_RESPONSE_SIZE_BYTES = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10MB

    // Network CIDR blocks to deny
    private static final String[] BLOCKED_CIDRS = {
        "127.0.0.0/8",      // Loopback
        "10.0.0.0/8",       // Private Class A
        "172.16.0.0/12",    // Private Class B
        "192.168.0.0/16",   // Private Class C
        "169.254.0.0/16",   // Link-local (AWS metadata)
        "100.64.0.0/10",    // Carrier-grade NAT
        "198.18.0.0/15",    // Benchmark testing
        "0.0.0.0/8",        // Current network
        "224.0.0.0/4",      // Multicast
        "240.0.0.0/4",      // Reserved
        "::1/128",          // IPv6 loopback
        "fc00::/7",         // IPv6 unique local
        "fe80::/10"         // IPv6 link-local
    };

    public ProductionSSRFSafeClient(MeterRegistry meterRegistry) {
        // Initialize DNS cache with short TTL to balance security/performance
        this.dnsCache = CacheBuilder.newBuilder()
            .expireAfterWrite(DNS_CACHE_TTL_SECONDS, TimeUnit.SECONDS)
            .maximumSize(10000)
            .build();

        this.rateLimiters = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

        // Production metrics
        this.ssrfBlockedCounter = meterRegistry.counter("ssrf.blocked.total");
        this.dnsRebindingAttempts = meterRegistry.counter("ssrf.dns_rebinding.detected");
        this.requestTimer = meterRegistry.timer("ssrf.safe_request.duration");

        // Disable DNS caching in JVM to ensure we always re-resolve
        Security.setProperty("networkaddress.cache.ttl", "0");
        Security.setProperty("networkaddress.cache.negative.ttl", "0");
    }

    public String fetchUrl(String urlString, String clientId) throws SSRFException {
        return requestTimer.record(() -> {
            try {
                return doSecureFetch(urlString, clientId);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                throw new RuntimeException(e);
            }
        });
    }

    private String doSecureFetch(String urlString, String clientId) throws Exception {
        // Step 1: Rate limiting
        if (!checkRateLimit(clientId)) {
            logger.warning(String.format("Rate limit exceeded for client: %s", clientId));
            throw new SSRFException("Rate limit exceeded");
        }

        // Step 2: Parse and validate URL structure
        URL url = parseAndValidateUrl(urlString);
        String host = url.getHost();

        // Step 3: DNS Resolution with caching (prevents rebinding)
        InetAddress[] resolvedAddresses = resolveDNSWithCache(host);

        // Step 4: Validate ALL resolved IPs
        for (InetAddress addr : resolvedAddresses) {
            if (!isAddressAllowed(addr)) {
                ssrfBlockedCounter.increment();
                logger.severe(String.format(
                    "SSRF BLOCKED: client=%s, url=%s, resolved_ip=%s",
                    clientId, urlString, addr.getHostAddress()));
                throw new SSRFException("Access to internal network denied");
            }
        }

        // Step 5: Make request using pinned IP (prevents DNS rebinding)
        return makeRequestWithPinnedIP(url, resolvedAddresses[0], clientId);
    }

    private URL parseAndValidateUrl(String urlString) throws SSRFException {
        try {
            URI uri = new URI(urlString).normalize();

            // Validate scheme
            String scheme = uri.getScheme();
            if (scheme == null || (!scheme.equalsIgnoreCase("http") && !scheme.equalsIgnoreCase("https"))) {
                throw new SSRFException("Invalid scheme: only HTTP/HTTPS allowed");
            }

            // Block userinfo
            if (uri.getUserInfo() != null) {
                throw new SSRFException("URLs with credentials not allowed");
            }

            // Validate host exists
            String host = uri.getHost();
            if (host == null || host.isEmpty()) {
                throw new SSRFException("Invalid or missing hostname");
            }

            // Block suspicious patterns in host
            if (host.contains("@") || host.contains("#") || host.contains("\\")) {
                throw new SSRFException("Invalid hostname characters");
            }

            // Validate port if specified
            int port = uri.getPort();
            if (port != -1 && !isPortAllowed(port)) {
                throw new SSRFException("Port not allowed: " + port);
            }

            return uri.toURL();
        } catch (URISyntaxException | MalformedURLException e) {
            throw new SSRFException("Malformed URL: " + e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    private InetAddress[] resolveDNSWithCache(String host) throws SSRFException {
        try {
            // Check cache first (prevents DNS rebinding)
            InetAddress[] cached = dnsCache.getIfPresent(host);
            if (cached != null) {
                return cached;
            }

            // Fresh DNS resolution
            InetAddress[] addresses = InetAddress.getAllByName(host);
            if (addresses == null || addresses.length == 0) {
                throw new SSRFException("DNS resolution failed");
            }

            // Cache the resolution
            dnsCache.put(host, addresses);
            return addresses;

        } catch (UnknownHostException e) {
            throw new SSRFException("DNS resolution failed: " + host);
        }
    }

    private boolean isAddressAllowed(InetAddress addr) {
        // Built-in Java checks
        if (addr.isLoopbackAddress() ||
            addr.isLinkLocalAddress() ||
            addr.isSiteLocalAddress() ||
            addr.isAnyLocalAddress() ||
            addr.isMulticastAddress()) {
            return false;
        }

        // Additional CIDR range checks
        byte[] addrBytes = addr.getAddress();

        // IPv4 specific checks
        if (addrBytes.length == 4) {
            int firstOctet = addrBytes[0] & 0xFF;
            int secondOctet = addrBytes[1] & 0xFF;

            // 169.254.x.x (AWS/cloud metadata)
            if (firstOctet == 169 && secondOctet == 254) return false;

            // 10.x.x.x
            if (firstOctet == 10) return false;

            // 172.16-31.x.x
            if (firstOctet == 172 && secondOctet >= 16 && secondOctet <= 31) return false;

            // 192.168.x.x
            if (firstOctet == 192 && secondOctet == 168) return false;

            // 100.64-127.x.x (Carrier-grade NAT)
            if (firstOctet == 100 && secondOctet >= 64 && secondOctet <= 127) return false;
        }

        return true;
    }

    private boolean isPortAllowed(int port) {
        // Whitelist of allowed ports
        return port == 80 || port == 443 || port == 8080 || port == 8443;
    }

    private String makeRequestWithPinnedIP(URL originalUrl, InetAddress pinnedIP, String clientId) 
            throws Exception {

        // Step 1: Create socket factory that connects to pinned IP
        // This prevents DNS rebinding during connection

        int port = originalUrl.getPort();
        if (port == -1) {
            port = originalUrl.getProtocol().equals("https") ? 443 : 80;
        }

        // Create connection to specific IP
        Socket socket = new Socket();
        socket.connect(new InetSocketAddress(pinnedIP, port), CONNECTION_TIMEOUT_MS);
        socket.setSoTimeout(READ_TIMEOUT_MS);

        // CRITICAL: Re-validate the connected IP (defense in depth)
        InetAddress connectedAddr = socket.getInetAddress();
        if (!isAddressAllowed(connectedAddr)) {
            socket.close();
            dnsRebindingAttempts.increment();
            logger.severe(String.format(
                "DNS REBINDING DETECTED: client=%s, expected=%s, connected=%s",
                clientId, pinnedIP.getHostAddress(), connectedAddr.getHostAddress()));
            throw new SSRFException("DNS rebinding attack detected");
        }

        try {
            // For HTTPS, wrap with SSL
            if (originalUrl.getProtocol().equals("https")) {
                SSLSocketFactory sslFactory = (SSLSocketFactory) SSLSocketFactory.getDefault();
                socket = sslFactory.createSocket(socket, originalUrl.getHost(), port, true);
            }

            // Send HTTP request
            OutputStream out = socket.getOutputStream();
            String request = String.format(
                "GET %s HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: %s\r\nConnection: close\r\n\r\n",
                originalUrl.getPath().isEmpty() ? "/" : originalUrl.getPath(),
                originalUrl.getHost());
            out.write(request.getBytes("UTF-8"));
            out.flush();

            // Read response with size limit
            InputStream in = socket.getInputStream();
            ByteArrayOutputStream buffer = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
            byte[] data = new byte[8192];
            int totalRead = 0;
            int bytesRead;

            while ((bytesRead = in.read(data)) != -1) {
                totalRead += bytesRead;
                if (totalRead > MAX_RESPONSE_SIZE_BYTES) {
                    throw new SSRFException("Response too large");
                }
                buffer.write(data, 0, bytesRead);
            }

            logger.info(String.format(
                "SSRF_SAFE_REQUEST: client=%s, url=%s, ip=%s, bytes=%d",
                clientId, originalUrl, pinnedIP.getHostAddress(), totalRead));

            return buffer.toString("UTF-8");

        } finally {
            socket.close();
        }
    }

    private boolean checkRateLimit(String clientId) {
        RateLimiter limiter = rateLimiters.computeIfAbsent(clientId, 
            k -> new RateLimiter(MAX_REQUESTS_PER_MINUTE));
        return limiter.tryAcquire();
    }

    // Simple rate limiter implementation
    private static class RateLimiter {
        private final int maxRequests;
        private final ConcurrentLinkedQueue<Long> timestamps = new ConcurrentLinkedQueue<>();

        RateLimiter(int maxPerMinute) {
            this.maxRequests = maxPerMinute;
        }

        synchronized boolean tryAcquire() {
            long now = System.currentTimeMillis();
            long windowStart = now - 60000;

            // Remove old timestamps
            while (!timestamps.isEmpty() && timestamps.peek() < windowStart) {
                timestamps.poll();
            }

            if (timestamps.size() >= maxRequests) {
                return false;
            }

            timestamps.add(now);
            return true;
        }
    }

    public static class SSRFException extends Exception {
        public SSRFException(String message) {
            super(message);
        }
    }
}
