**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- URL class and axios parse URLs differently, especially malformed ones
- BLOCKED_HOSTS uses `includes()` which misses IP variants (decimal, octal, IPv6)
- No resolution of hostname to actual IP before blocking check
- DNS rebinding can make a 'safe' domain resolve to internal IPs

**SECURE VERSION**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const axios = require('axios');
const { URL } = require('url');
const dns = require('dns').promises;
const ipaddr = require('ipaddr.js');

const app = express();
